<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="354" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1863,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1863,1888]" pageId="4" pageNumber="354">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Most similar in combination of characters (see key) to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Stichel, 1923" authorityName="Stichel" authorityYear="1923" box="[1087,1382,1863,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Eocarterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1087,1211,1865,1888]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="354">Eocarterus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1225,1382,1863,1888]" pageId="4" pageNumber="354" refId="ref14177" refString="Stichel, W. (1923) Zur Phylogenesis eines geologisch jungen Formenkreises der Kafer, der Ditominen (Carab. Harpal.). Zeitschrift fur wissenschaftliche Insektenbiologie, 18, 41 - 50 + 81 - 100 + 145 - 162 + 209 - 242." type="journal article">Stichel, 1923</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but distinguished by having head relatively wider, mentum without median tooth, labrum more deeply concave anteriorly, pronotum not cordate, its sides largely rounded, with very short and shallow sinuation just before basal angles. From the species of subgenus 
<emphasis box="[573,721,1973,1996]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="354">Baeticocarus</emphasis>
Jeanne, 1971, the member of the new genus additionally differs in complete basal elytral border (
<taxonomicName authority="Kаtаev &amp; Wrаse, 2018" authorityName="Kаtаev &amp; Wrаse" authorityYear="2018" box="[522,646,2009,2032]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Eocarterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto" status="s. str.">
<emphasis box="[522,646,2009,2032]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="354">Eocarterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[653,712,2009,2032]" pageId="4" pageNumber="354" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has incomplete basal border as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kаtаev &amp; Wrаse, 2018" authorityName="Kаtаev &amp; Wrаse" authorityYear="2018" box="[1098,1243,2008,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Indocarterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1098,1243,2008,2033]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="354">Indocarterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1249,1327,2008,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="354" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1249,1327,2008,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="354">gen. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="355" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1184]" box="[199,1086,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Description</emphasis>
. Dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[456,556,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 5, 6" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1392,1415]" captionTargetBox="[192,1402,451,1356]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[163,1427,432,1382]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5, 6. Indocarterus inexspectatus sp. n., habitus. 5, male holotype; 6, female paratype. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458713/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
) and venter rather densely punctate and setose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">
Head large, slightly narrower than pronotum, constricted behind eyes, with only one long seta near inner margin of eyes on each side. Lateral margin of frons (
<figureCitation box="[799,872,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[234,1316,203,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1846]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Indocarterus inexspectatus sp. n. (paratypes: 7, 8 female; 9, male). 7, anterior part of head; 8, pronotum; 9, protarsus and apical part of protibia. 7, 8, dorsal view; 9, lateral view. Scales bars = 1.0 mm (A, C: Figs 7, 9; B: Fig. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458715/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) above insertion of antennae angularly rounded anteriorly. Labrum deeply concave anteriorly. Clypeus along anterior margin without convex smooth bead, rather deeply arcuately emarginate, and membranous base of labrum exposed. Genae wide. Mentum (
<figureCitation box="[1249,1333,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1206,1229]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,620,1169]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,589,1185]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 10–17. Indocarterus inexspectatus sp. n. (paratypes). 10, labium; 11, apex of median lobe; 12, 13, median lobe; 14, left paramere, inner surface; 15, left paramere, inner surface; 16, stylus, 17, right laterotergite and stylus. 10, 17, ventral view; 11, 13, dorsal view; 12, 14–16, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm (Fig. 10), B = 0.5 mm (Figs 11–16)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458717/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) without median tooth, separated from submentum by complete transverse suture. Ligular sclerite not widened at apex, without ventral plate, and with several rather long, visible in ventral view, dorsal setae in addition to two ventral distal setae. Paraglossae rather narrow, glabrous at margins. Terminal maxillary and labial palpomeres more or less cylindrical, narrowed distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[328,398,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[234,1316,203,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1846]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Indocarterus inexspectatus sp. n. (paratypes: 7, 8 female; 9, male). 7, anterior part of head; 8, pronotum; 9, protarsus and apical part of protibia. 7, 8, dorsal view; 9, lateral view. Scales bars = 1.0 mm (A, C: Figs 7, 9; B: Fig. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458715/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) not cordate, its sides not serrate, largely rounded, with very short and shallow prebasal sinuation sharply delimited anteriorly (see remarks).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Mesothorax and extreme base of elytra narrowed forming a very short neck-like constriction with scutellum above. Elytra not serrate at sides, basal border complete, strongly bent and raised near scutellum.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Three penultimate abdominal sternites, in addition to short and dense pubescence, only with two obligatory long setae along posterior margin.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">
Metacoxa without posteromedial setigerous pore. Profemur not denticulate along inner margin. Metatrochanter short, about a third as long as metafemur, rounded at apex. Protibia without long, finger-like acute apical process, with three or four preapical spines on outer margin, densely setose on ventral surface. Tarsi densely setose dorsally. Protarsus and mesotarsus of male not dilated and without ventral adhesive vestiture. Protarsomeres 1, 2 and 3 (sometimes also 4) each of both sexes with a short acute spine in middle of ventro-apical margin (
<figureCitation box="[1347,1422,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[234,1316,203,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1846]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Indocarterus inexspectatus sp. n. (paratypes: 7, 8 female; 9, male). 7, anterior part of head; 8, pronotum; 9, protarsus and apical part of protibia. 7, 8, dorsal view; 9, lateral view. Scales bars = 1.0 mm (A, C: Figs 7, 9; B: Fig. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458715/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Metatarsomere 1 scarcely shorter than 2+3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="355" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,908,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Etymology</emphasis>
. The genus name is a combination of the name of the country 
<collectingCountry box="[1049,1108,908,933]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis box="[1049,1108,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">India</emphasis>
</collectingCountry>
and the name of the carabid genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1830" box="[223,323,944,967]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Carterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[223,323,944,967]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Carterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,557,980,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Composition and distribution</emphasis>
. The genus includes only one species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kаtаev &amp; Wrаse, 2018" authorityName="Kаtаev &amp; Wrаse" authorityYear="2018" box="[1014,1192,981,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Indocarterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inexspectatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1014,1192,981,1004]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">I. inexspectatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1202,1268,980,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1202,1268,980,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from western India (
<figureCitation box="[224,308,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1105,1127]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,195,1083]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,195,1083]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 24. Geographical range of the subtribe Ditomina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458721/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="355" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1052,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Remarks</emphasis>
. It is possible that the short and shallow prebasal sinuation of pronotal sides (
<figureCitation box="[1210,1279,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[234,1316,203,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1846]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Indocarterus inexspectatus sp. n. (paratypes: 7, 8 female; 9, male). 7, anterior part of head; 8, pronotum; 9, protarsus and apical part of protibia. 7, 8, dorsal view; 9, lateral view. Scales bars = 1.0 mm (A, C: Figs 7, 9; B: Fig. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458715/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) is actually a lateral part of pronotal base as in the members of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Stephens, 1825" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1825" box="[911,1217,1087,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philochtus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[911,1031,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Philochtus</emphasis>
Stephens, 1825
</taxonomicName>
(genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1315,1437,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Bembidion</emphasis>
Latreille, 1802
</taxonomicName>
). In this case the pronotal sides of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kаtаev &amp; Wrаse, 2018" authorityName="Kаtаev &amp; Wrаse" authorityYear="2018" box="[725,870,1124,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Indocarterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[725,870,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Indocarterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[879,960,1124,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[879,960,1124,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">gen. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are rounded to basal angles, but the base inside them is sinuate and the basal pronotal angles are correspondingly shifted from the base anteriad.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
